# Shed Configurator – AI Agent Rules

This project is a 3D Bramwood shed configurator. Follow these rules to work efficiently and avoid unnecessary changes.

---

## 1. Project Purpose

- 3D Bramwood shed configurator for designing shed structure only
- Covers: shed size, roof type, wall-by-wall openings, internal partitions, framing visualization, cladding, roof
- **Not** an interior furnishing planner unless explicitly requested
- No furniture, shelves, or workbenches

---

## 2. Files to Read First

Before making changes, read:

- `docs/PROJECT_ARCHITECTURE.md`
- `docs/SYSTEM_MAP.md`
- `docs/BUILD_RULES.md`
- `docs/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDELINES.md`

---

## 3. Protected Systems

Do **not** modify unless explicitly requested:

- ConfiguratorContext core dimension logic
- shedData.json structure
- builderStep workflow
- Existing window drag behavior
- Existing door drag behavior
- Camera control behavior
- Core shed dimension math

---

## 4. Bramwood Defaults

| Rule | Value |
|------|-------|
| Apex standard wall height | 66" |
| Apex workshop wall height | 70" |
| Pent back wall | 70" |
| Pent front wall | 70" + shed depth (feet) |
| Standard window | 24" × 24" |
| Security window | 24" × 12" |
| Single door clear opening | 27" |
| Double door opening | 60" |
| Stud spacing | 24" |
| Noggins | ~36" vertically |
| Cladding | Horizontal shiplap |
| Board width | 5" |
| Visible coverage | ~4" |

---

## 5. Interaction Rules

- Windows must be draggable on all walls from either side
- Openings snap to 6" grid
- Stud assist can use 24" spacing
- Camera / orbit controls must lock during active dragging
- Wall grid appears only during selection/drag and disappears when cleared

---

## 6. Rendering Rules

- Use the live mounted render path
- Do not add unused replacement components
- Confirm the real render chain before broad visual changes

---

## 7. Performance Rules

- No heavy work every frame
- Do not reset camera every frame
- Use `useMemo` for geometry and layout
- Prefer `InstancedMesh` for repeated framing elements

---

## 8. Preferred Change Style

- Audit before modifying
- Prefer the smallest safe change
- Isolate changes by system
- Prefer shared helpers over hardcoded dimensions
- Prioritize stability

---

## 9. Documentation Behavior

- Update the docs folder if architecture changes significantly
- Do not document features that are not in the code

---

## 10. Current Priorities

1. Keep the configurator stable
2. Preserve working drag behavior
3. Match openings to Bramwood rules
4. Improve realism
5. Improve framing accuracy
6. Improve maintainability
